table = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6 ,7, 8, 9}

def multiply(x, y, /):
    return x * y

def print_output(x, y, /):
    out = f"{x} x {y} = {multiply(x, y)}"
    print(out, end='|')

for x in table:
    for y in table:
        print_output(x, y)
    print('\n')
